        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Thanks, that concern makes sense. My intent here was to keep the change narrow: only exact duplicates after conversion to quickfix entries are collapsed, and distinct ranges from different servers are still preserved.\n\nI am less sure about a health warning as the primary fix. Capability overlap by itself can be valid, and whether two servers produce redundant locations is request-dependent, so a warning could be noisy unless we have a stronger signal than shared `definitionProvider`/`referencesProvider` capabilities.\n\nIf the preference is to avoid doing this in `get_locations()` entirely, I can rework or close this. If exact duplicate suppression at the aggregation point is acceptable, I can also add a short note to the test/implementation to make that scope clearer.",
